"title": "4819: dryness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4819",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A lack of moisture, often due to lack of rain or a period of drought, leading to vegetation drying up. Dryness is often used as a symbol of hopelessness or of the absence of God's blessing.</p>\n<h2>The dryness of river beds</h2>\n<h3>Evaporation and recession of floodwaters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:13-Gen8:14\">GEN 8:13–8:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:1-Gen8:11\">GEN 8:1–8:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's drying up of rivers to allow his people to cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:23\">JOS 4:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:10-Exod14:31\">EXO 14:10–14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:10\">JOS 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:1-Josh3:17\">JOS 3:1–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:1\">JOS 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:7-Ps106:11\">PSA 106:7–106:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:15\">ISA 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:10\">ISA 51:10</a></p>\n<h3>Other instances of rivers drying up</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:7\">1KI 17:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:24\">2KI 19:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:25\">ISA 37:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:15\">PSA 74:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa15:6\">ISA 15:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:4-Isa19:10\">ISA 19:4–19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:15\">ISA 42:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:24-Isa44:27\">ISA 44:24–44:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:2\">ISA 50:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:34\">JER 48:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:36\">JER 51:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:12\">EZK 30:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:20\">JOL 1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:4\">NAM 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>The dryness of vegetation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:2\">PSA 37:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:11-Job8:12\">JOB 8:11–8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:19\">JOB 8:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:2\">JOB 14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:30\">JOB 15:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:4\">ISA 34:4</a> <em>on the day of the LORD</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:7-Isa40:8\">ISA 40:7–40:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:13\">JER 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:4\">JER 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10-Ezek19:14\">EZK 19:10–19:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:16\">HOS 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:3-Matt13:6\">MAT 13:3–13:6</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:2-Mark4:6\">MRK 4:2–4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:4-Luke8:6\">LUK 8:4–8:6</a> <em>the parable of the sower</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:19-Matt21:20\">MAT 21:19–21:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:20-Mark11:21\">MRK 11:20–11:21</a> <em>the fig-tree withers</em></p>\n<h2>Physical dryness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:11\">EZK 37:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:4\">PSA 102:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:11\">PSA 102:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:22\">PRO 17:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:17\">ZEC 11:17</a></p>\n<h2>Dryness indicative of desolation and hopelessness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:12\">JOL 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:7\">ISA 24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:9\">ISA 33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:10\">JER 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:10\">JOL 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:17\">JOL 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:5\">ZEC 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:11\">ZEC 10:11</a></p>\n<h2>Dryness indicating God's withholding of moisture due to sin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:22-Deut28:24\">DEU 28:22–28:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:35-1Kgs8:36\">1KI 8:35–8:36</a></p>",
